metric tons of naphtha by tender to PetroChina Co. for loading
from the port of Vadinar from March 14 to March 18, ICIS
reported today, citing unidentified traders.  The cargo was sold at a $12.50 a ton premium to Middle East
prices, according to ICIS.  PetroChina also bought by tender from Bharat Petroleum
Corp. 30,000 tons of the fuel for loading from March 13 to March
15, ICIS said. The shipment was sold at a premium of $13.28 a
ton to Middle East prices, according to ICIS.  To contact the reporter on this story:
